text: Renzo Chiocchetti (17 November 1945 – 13 February 2020) was an Italian cross- country skier. He was born in Moena. He competed at the 1972 Winter Olympics and the 1976 Winter Olympics. He died in Moena at the age of 74. ==References== ==Other websites== *Renzo Chiocchetti at Sports-Reference.com Category:1945 births Category:2020 deaths Category:1972 Winter Olympics Category:Olympians for Italy Category:Italian skiers Category:Competitors at the 1976 Winter Olympics Category:People from Trentino-Alto Adige/Südtirol
